title: Grateful Dead Live at Three Rivers Stadium on 1990-07-08

description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Jack A Roe, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah-> Eyes Of The World-> Estimated Prophet-> Terrapin Station-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Wang Dang Doodle-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

Crosby Stills & Nash Opened

reviews.review_text: Su90 Tour N3: View From the Vault  Big fan of this show, perhaps on account of the dvd. Remember its release back in 2000, fondly.

On Fire It's no wonder they chose this as the first View From The Vault. I was there and it was a helluva night. CSN opened with Love The One You're With and it only got better. I was in the 30th row on the field and it was hot as hell that day. Hoses kept the crowd cooled down and the band just kept on making it hotter. You can't see it on the DVD, but during Estimated, Weir rushed the front of the stage several times. Listen to the crowd cheer. The Terrapin>Drums>Space>Miracle is one of my favorites. And the leg fell off the dancing skeleton during Miracle (or did I just imagine that?). They didn't announce this show for a while, but we all suspected, as there was a gap between shows. We partied all night and stood in line to get wristbands for the tickets. Luckily, we were fourth in line. We were rewarded with what would be my last time at Three Rivers.
Thank you Have a nice day 😊
